11/11/2003
LONDON, United Kingdom -- Serbia-Montenegro Defence Minister Boris Tadic met with British Defence Secretary Geoffrey Hoon and Foreign Secretary Jack Straw on Monday (10 November).
The officials discussed the pace of military reforms and steps Serbia needs to take to enter NATO's Partnership for Peace programme.
Tadic said his hosts clearly indicated that the failure to apprehend Bosnian Serb General Ratko Mladic is a major obstacle to bilateral relations and Alliance aspirations.
In other news Monday, France urged Kosovo to engage in direct talks with Belgrade.
Paris said it wants to see UNMIK and Pristina complete a working plan on how to meet the standards required before status talks could begin.
(BBC, B92, BKVT, Tanjug - 10/11/03)
